author: seank11
body:
Yes I am. The have great margins, great revs, and a very low valuation.

There is a chip shortage, and MU manufacturs the components that go into many of these chips. This gives MU pricing power, and since the industry is now an oligopoly where the players are limiting CapEx and thus not increasing production too much, there will probably be a run on pricing in the next contract negotiations.

Wouldnt be surprised to see MU hit 100 by EOM, and I believe March 4 has the CEO speaking, where I personally believe they will announce 2 of: Raising guidance, increased BuyBacks, or a divvy.

I will probably be buying VERY short dated OTM calls before this conference, hoping to get a 10 bagger lotto ticket.
